dns-proxy (1.2.0-1) bookworm; urgency=medium

  This release introduces support for multiple upstream DNS servers,
  providing high availability and load distribution for production
  deployments.
  
  Configuration changes:
  - New 'server-addresses' field accepts comma-separated list of servers
  - Supports mixed IPv4/IPv6 servers with optional custom ports
  - Backward compatible - existing single-server configs still work
  
  Example configuration:
    [forwarder-dns]
    server-addresses = 1.1.1.1,8.8.8.8,[2606:4700:4700::1111]:53
  
  Benefits:
  - Automatic failover if primary DNS server fails
  - Round-robin load distribution
  - No single point of failure
  - Mix internal and external DNS servers
  
  See /usr/share/doc/dns-proxy/docs/multiple-dns-servers.md for details.

 -- Philip S. Hempel <pshempel@linuxsrc.com>  Sat, 11 Jan 2025 18:00:00 -0500